<h3>Studies of Illustration, Victorian and Earlier</h3>

<p class="bibl"><p class="bibl">Anderson, Patricia J. <span class="book">The Printed Image and the Transformation of Popular Culture, 1790–1860</span>. Oxford: Clarendon Press, 1991.</p>

<p class="bibl">Bland, David. <span class="book">A History of Book Illustration</span>. London: Faber, 1969.</p>

<p class ="bibl"> Golden, Catherine J. (Ed). <span class ="book">Book Illustrated: Text, Image, and Culture, 1770–1930</span> Delaware: Oak Knoll Press, 2000. </p>

<p class ="bibl"> Gray, Basil. <span class ="book">The English Print</span>. London: Black, 1937.</p>

<p class="bibl">Hillis Miller, J. <span class="book">Illustration</span>. London: Reaktion Press, 1992.</p>

<p class="bibl">Hodnett, Edward. <span class="book">Five Centuries of English Book Illustration</span>. Aldershot: Scolar, 1988. </p>

<p class="bibl">Hodnett, Edward. <span class="book">Image and Text</span>. Aldershot: Scolar, 1982. </p>

<p class="bibl">James, Philip. <span class="book">English book illustration, 1800-1900</span>. London: Penguin,1947.</p>

<p class="bibl">Maidment, Brian. <span class="book">Comedy, Caricature and the Social Order, 1820–50</span>. Manchester, UK: Manchester University Press, 2013.</p>

<h3>General Studies and Accounts of Victorian Illustration, 1837–1901: Style, Idiom, Theme, Technique</h3>

<p class ="bibl">Buchanan-Brown, John.  <span class ="book">Early Victorian Illustrated Books</span>. London: The British Library, 2005. </p>

<p class ="bibl">Cooke, Simon. <span class ="book">Illustrated Periodicals of the 1860s</span>.Pinner: The Private Libraries Association and The British Library, 2010.</p>

<p class = "bibl">Dalziel, George & Edward. <span class = "book">A Record of  Fifty Years’ Work</span>. 1901; rpt. London: Batsford, 1978.</p>

<p class = "bibl">Daniels, Morna. <span class = "book">Victorian Book Illustration</span>. London: The British Library, 1988.</p>

<p class ="bibl">de Maré, Eric. <span class="illustration">The Victorian Woodblock Illustrators</span>. London: Gordon Fraser, 1980.</p>

<p class ="bibl"> Engen, Rodney. <span class ="book">Pre-Raphaelite Prints</span>. London: Lund Humphries, 1995. </p>

<p class="bibl">Golden, Catherine J. <span class="book">Serials to Graphic Novels: The Evolution of the Victorian Illustrated Book</span>. Gainesville: University Press of Florida, 2017.</p> 

<p class = "bibl">Goldman, Paul. <span class = "book">Children’s Illustration in the Sixties</span>. Children’s Books History Society, Occasional Paper 4 (October 1995). </p>

<p class ="bibl"> Goldman, Paul. <span class ="book">Victorian Illustrated Books, 1850–1870: The Heyday of Wood Engraving</span>. London: The British Museum, 1994.</p>

<p class ="bibl">Goldman, Paul. <span class ="book">Victorian Illustration: the Pre-Raphaelites, the Idyllic School and the High Victorians</span>. Aldershot: Scolar, 1996; new ed. London: Lund Humphries, 2004. </p>

<p class="bibl">Hardie, Martin. <span class="book">English Coloured Books</span>. 1909; Totowa, NJ: Rowman and Littlefield, 1973.</p>

<p class ="bibl"> Houfe, Simon. <span class ="book">The Dictionary of Nineteenth Century British Book Illustrators</span>. Woodbridge: Antique Collectors’ Club, 1988.</p>

<p class="bibl">Kooistra, Lorraine Janzen. <span class="book">The Artist as Critic: Bitextuality in Fin-de-Siecle Illustrated Books</span>. Aldershot: Scolar, 1997.</p>

<p class = "bibl">Kooistra, Lorraine Janzen. <span class="book">Christina Rossetti and Illustration: A Publishing History</span>. Athens: Ohio University Press, 2002.</p>

<p class = "bibl">Kooistra, Lorraine Janzen. ‘Science and Art: Vestiges of Corpses in Pre-Raphaelite Illustrations’. <span class = "book">Reading Victorian Illustration, 1855–1875 </span>.   Eds. Paul Goldman and Simon Cooke. Burlington, V.T: Ashgate, 2012. 97–114. </p>

<p class ="bibl">Maxwell, Richard (Ed). <span class ="book">The Victorian Illustrated Book</span>. Charlottesville: University of Virginia Press, 2002.</p>

<p class = "bibl"> Muir, Percy. <span class="book">Victorian Illustrated Books</span>. London: Batsford, 1971; revised ed., 1985.</p>

<p class="bibl">Pennell, Joseph. <span class="book">Modern Illustration</span>. London: Bell, 1895. </p>

<p class = "bibl">Ray, Gordon. <span class = "book">The Illustrator and the Book in England from 1790 to 1914</span>.  New York: Pierpont Morgan Library, 1976.</p>

<p class ="bibl">Reid, Forrest. <span class ="book">Illustrators of the Eighteen Sixties</span>. 1928; rpt. New York: Dover, 1975. </p>

<p class="bibl">Sketchley, R. E. D. <span class ="book">English Illustration of Today</span>. London: Kegan Paul, Trench, Trübner and Co., 1903.</p>

<p class = "bibl">Skoblow, Jeffrey. ‘Beyond Reading: Kelmscott and the Modern.’ <span class = "book">The Victorian Illustrated Book</span>. Ed. Richard Maxwell.  Charlottesville: The University Press of Virginia, 2002. 239–258. </p>

<p class ="bibl"> Spielmann, M. H. <span class ="book">The History of Punch</span>. London: Cassell, 1895.</p>

<p class ="bibl"> Suriano, Gregory. <span class ="book">The Pre-Raphaelite Illustrators</span>. London: British Library, 2000.</p>

<p class="bibl">Thomas, Julia. ‘Happy Endings: Death and Domesticity in Victorian Illustration.’ <span class="book">Reading Victorian Illustration, 1855–75.</span>. Eds. Paul Goldman and Simon Cooke. Burlington: Ashgate, 2012. 79–96.</p> 
	
<p class="bibl">Thomas, Julia. <span class="book">Pictorial Victorians</span>. Athens, Ohio: Ohio University Press, 2004.</p> 
	
<p class ="bibl"> Vaughan, William. ‘Facsimile versus White Line: An Anglo-German Disparity.’ <span class ="book">Reading Victorian Illustration, 1855–1875</span>. Eds. Paul Goldman and Simon Cooke. Burlington VT: Ashgate, 2012. 33–52.</p>	

<p class ="bibl">Wakeman, Geoffrey. <span class ="book">Victorian Illustration: The Technical Revolution</span>. Newton Abbot: David & Charles, 1973.</p>

<p class="bibl">White, Gleeson. <span class="book">English Illustration, ‘The Sixties’: 1855 –70</span>. London: Constable, 1897.</p>

<h3>Monographs of Illustrators and Related Articles </h3>

<p class ="bibl">Christian, John. ‘Burne-Jones’s Drawings for <span class = "book">The Fairy Family</span>.’ <span class = "periodical">The Burlington Magazine</span> 115 (February 1973): 93–100.</p>

<p class ="bibl">Collins, Jeffrey Laird. ‘Prototype, Posing, and Preference in the Illustrations of Frederick Sandys and Simeon Solomon.’ <span class="book">Pocket Cathedrals: Pre-Raphaelite Illustration</span>. Ed. Susan Casteras. New Haven: Yale Center for British Art, 1991. 79–92. </p>
	
<p class="bibl">Cooke, Simon. ‘“Sustained Power”: The Life and Art of William Small.’ <span class="periodical">The IBIS Journal</span> 6 (2018): 87–139.</p>

<p class="bibl">[Cruikshank, George]. <span class="book">George Cruikshank</span>. Intro. William Feaver. Exhibition catalogue. London: Arts Council, 1974.</p>

<p class = "bibl">Elzea, Betty. <span class = "book">Frederick Sandys, 1829–1904.</span>. Woodbridge: Antiques Collectors’ Club, 2001. </p>

<p class="bibl">Engen, Rodney. <span class="book">Kate Greenaway: A Biography</span>. New York: Schocken, 1981. </p>

<p class = "bibl">Engen, Rodney. <span class="book">Laurence Housman</span>. Stroud: The Catalpa Press, 1983.</p>

<p class = "bibl">Engen, Rodney. <span class="book">Richard Doyle</span>. Stroud: The Catalpa Press, 1983.</p>

<p class = "bibl">Golden, Catherine. ‘Beatrix Potter: Naturalist Artist.’ <span class="periodical">Woman's Art Journal</span> 11, 1 (Spring–Summer, 1990): 16 –20.</p> 

<p class="bibl">Goldman, Paul. ‘George Du Maurier as a Draughtsman and Illustrator.’ <span class="book">George Du Maurier: Illustrator, Author, Critic.
</span>. Eds. Simon Cooke & Paul Goldman. Farnham: Ashgate, 2016. 17–31. </p>

<p class="bibl">Hogarth, Paul. <span class="book">Arthur Boyd Houghton</span>. London: Gordon Fraser, 1981.</p>

<p class ="bibl">Houfe, Simon. <span class ="book">The Work of Charles Samuel Keene.</span>. Aldershot: Scolar, 1995.</p>

<p class ="bibl">Lambourne, Lionel. <span class = "book">Ernest Griset: Fantasies of a Victorian Illustrator.</span> London: Thames & Hudson, 1979. </p>
	
<p class = "bibl">MacCulloch, Laura. ‘“Fleshing Out”’ Time: Ford Madox Brown and the Dalziels’ <span class="book">Bible Gallery</span>.’ <span class = "book">Reading Victorian Illustration, 1855–1875</span>. Eds. Paul Goldman and Simon Cooke. Burlington VT: Ashgate, 2012. 115–135. </p>

<p class ="bibl">McLean, Ruari. <span class="book">George Cruikshank: His Life and Work as a Book Illustrator</span>. English Masters of Black-and-White. London: Art and Technics, 1948.</p>

<p class="bibl">Oakley, Maroussia. <span class="book">The Book and Periodical Illustrations of Arthur Hughes</span>. Pinner: PLA & New Castle, Delaware: Oak Knoll Press, 2016.</p>

<p class="bibl">Patten, Robert L. <span class ="book">George Cruikshank's Life, Times, and Art</span>. 2 vols. New Brunswick, N.J.: Rutgers University Press, 1992-1996.</p>

<p class = "bibl">Reynolds, Jan. <span class = "book">Birket Foster</span>.  London: Batsford, 1984. </p>

<p class = "bibl">Spencer, Isobel. <span class ="book">Walter Crane</span>. New York: Macmillan, 1975. </p>

<h3>Illustrating the Victorian Novel</h3>

<p class="bibl">Allingham, Philip V. ‘The Illustrations for <span class = "book">Great Expectations</span> in <span class = "periodical">Harper's Weekly</span> (1860-61) and in the Illustrated Library Edition (1862) — “Reading by the Light of Illustration.”’ <span class = "periodical">Dickens Studies Annual</span> 40 (Spring 2009): 113–69.</p>

<p class="bibl">Allingham, Philip V. ‘Robert Barnes’s Illustrations for Thomas Hardy’s <span class="book">The Mayor of Casterbridge</span> as Serialised in <span class="periodical">The Graphic</span>.’ <span class="periodical">Victorian Periodicals Review</span> 28, 1 (Spring, 1995): 27–39.</p>

<p class="bibl">Allingham, Philip V. ‘Dicken’s <span class="book">A Tale of Two Cities</span> Illustrated: A Critical Reassessment of Hablôt Knight Browne’s Plates.’ <span class="periodical">Dickens Studies Annual</span>  33 (October, 2003): 109–157.</p>

<p class="bibl">Cohen, Jane. <span class="book">Charles Dickens and His Original Illustrators</span>. Columbus, Ohio: Ohio State University Press, 1980).</p>

<p class ="bibl">Cooke, Simon. ‘George du Maurier’s Illustrations for M.E. Braddon’s <span class ="book">Eleanor’s Victory</span> in <span class ="periodical">Once a Week</span>.’ <span class ="periodical">Victorian Periodicals Review</span> 35:1 (Spring 2002): 89–106.</p>

<p class ="bibl"> Du Maurier, George. ‘The Illustrating of Books from the Serious Artist’s Point of View.’ <span class ="book">The Magazine of Art</span> (1890): 349–53; 371–75. </p>

<p class="bibl">Fisher, Judith. ‘Image versus Text in the Illustrated Novels of William Makepeace Thackeray.’ <span class ="book">Victorian Literature and the Victorian Visual Imagination</span>. Eds. Carol T. Christ and John O. Jordan. Berkeley: University of California Press, 1995. pp. 60–87. </p>

<p class="bibl">Hall, N. John. <span class ="book">Trollope and His Illustrators</span>.  New York: St Martin's Press, 1980.</p>

<p class="bibl">Hancher, Michael. <span class="book">The Tenniel Illustrations to the “Alice” Books</span>. Columbus, OH: Ohio State UP, 1985. </p>

<p class="bibl">Harvey, John. <span class="book">Victorian Novelists and their Illustrators</span>. London: Sidgwick and Jackson, 1970.</p>

<p class="bibl">Hill, Richard. <span class="book">Robert Louis Stevenson and the Pictorial Text</span>. New York: Routledge, 2017.</p>

<p class="bibl">Jackson, Arlene M. <span class="book">Illustration and the Novels of Thomas Hardy</span>. Rowman and Littlefield, 1981.</p>

<p class="bibl">Kitton, Frederic G. <span class="book">Dickens and His Illustrators</span>. Chapman & Hall, 1899. [Rpt. Honolulu: U. Press of the Pacific, 2004.]</p>

<p class="bibl">Leighton, Mary Elizabeth, and Lisa Surridge. <span class="book">The Plot Thickens – Illustrated Victorian Serial Fiction from Dickens to Du Maurier</span>. Athens Ohio: Ohio University Press, 2019. </p>
	
<p class="bibl">Meisel, Martin. Chapter 13, "Novels in Epitome." <span class="book">Realizations: Narrative, Pictorial, and Theatrical Arts in Nineteenth-Century England</span>. Princeton: Princeton University Press, 1989.  
247–282.</p>

<p class="bibl">Steig, Michael. <span class="book">Dickens and Phiz</span>. Bloomington & London: Indiana U. P., 1978. [<a href="../phiz/steig/1.html">Complete text</a> on this site.]</p>

<p class = "bibl">Stevens, Joan. ‘Thackeray’s Pictorial Capitals.’ <span class ="periodical">Costerus</span> n.s. 2 (1974): 114–40. </p>
	
<h3>Illustrating Victorian Poetry</h3>

<p class="bibl">Cooke, Simon. <span class="book">The Moxon Tennyson: A Landmark in Victorian Illustration</span>. Athens, Ohio: Ohio University Press, 2021.</p>

<p class="bibl">Kooistra, Lorraine Janzen. ‘From Blake to Beardsley:  “On Some of the Characteristics of Modern Poetry.”’ <span class="periodical">Victorian Poetry</span>  48, 1 (Spring 2010): 1–9.</p>

<p class="bibl">Kooistra, Lorraine Janzen. ‘Making Poetry" in “<span class="periodical">Good Words</span>: Why Illustration Matters to Periodical Poetry Studies.’ <span class="periodical">Victorian Poetry</span> 52, 1 (Spring, 2014): 111–139.</p>

<p class="bibl">Kooistra, Lorraine Janzen. <span class="book">Poetry, Pictures, and Popular Publishing: The Illustrated Gift Book and Victorian Visual Culture, 1855–1875</span>.  Athens, Ohio: Ohio University Press, 2014.</p>

